a great intellectual to create the spark to ignite your civilization,
一位伟大的知识分子来点燃你们的文明

1232
01:10:26,440 --> 01:10:29,520
okay? So in Greece, they had Homer,
好的？在希腊，他们有荷马，

1233
01:10:29,680 --> 01:10:32,960
and today we can think of Homer as the father of civilization.
今天我们可以把荷马当作文明之父。

1234
01:10:34,460 --> 01:10:37,160
In the Italian Renaissance, you had Dante.
在意大利文艺复兴时期，你有但丁。

1235
01:10:37,320 --> 01:10:39,540
You can think of him as the father of modernity.
你可以把他当作现代性的父亲。

1236
01:10:39,680 --> 01:10:42,740
The values that he creates, the values that
他创造的价值观， 他所表达的价值观， 他在喜剧中所拥有的价值观将成为现代性的基础。

1237
01:10:42,740 --> 01:10:47,900
he expresses, the values that he has in the line comedy will become the basis for modernity,
he expresses, the values that he has in the line comedy will become the basis for modernity,

1238
01:10:47,960 --> 01:10:51,080
especially the idea of individuality, of humanism, right?
尤其是个体性、人的主义的观念，对吧？

1239
01:10:52,340 --> 01:10:56,000
What is an individual? An individual is someone who celebrates himself
个体是什么？个体是自我庆祝的人，

1240
01:10:56,400 --> 01:11:00,980
and pursues his or her curiosity to explore the world
他或她追随好奇去探世界

1241
01:11:00,980 --> 01:11:05,320
and in this process create goodness in the world,
并在此过程中在世界中创造善良，并创造真理与美感。

1242
01:11:05,360 --> 01:11:08,960
to create truth and beauty. This is the idea that will underpin the Renaissance
这就是支撑文艺复兴的理念，也仍是西方现代性与现代世界的基石。

1243
01:11:09,300 --> 01:11:12,900
and which still underpins Western modernity and the modern world.
and which still underpins Western modernity and the modern world.

1244
01:11:14,880 --> 01:11:20,440
So, what is the ultimate message?
那么，最终的意思是什么？

1245
01:11:24,500 --> 01:11:26,160
The ultimate message is the ultimate secret of the universe.
最终的意思就是宇宙的终极秘密。

1246
01:11:26,260 --> 01:11:27,560
I want you to remember, okay?
我想让你记住，好吗？

1247
01:11:27,620 --> 01:11:30,440
And both Homer and Dante expressed this in their poetry.
并且荷马与但丁都在诗中表达了这一点。

1248
01:11:30,580 --> 01:11:34,880
It's this. Love is the unifying force of the universe,
这就是了。爱是宇宙的统一力量，

1249
01:11:35,140 --> 01:11:37,100
okay? Love is God.
好吧？爱即是上帝。

1250
01:11:37,260 --> 01:11:40,940
God is love. It's what unites everyone, okay?
上帝是爱。它把大家统一在一起，好吗？

1251
01:11:41,040 --> 01:11:43,400
By loving someone else, you can become that person.
通过爱别人，你可以成为那个人。

1252
01:11:43,460 --> 01:11:45,180
So, you can become that person. That person can become you.
于是，你就能成为那个人。那个人又能成为你。

1253
01:11:45,400 --> 01:11:49,800
And the imagination is the animating force, okay?
并且想象是动能的力量，好吗？

1254
01:11:49,900 --> 01:11:53,540
What gives life to the world is not God, but our imagination.
给世界生命的不是上帝，而是我们的想象。

1255
01:11:54,120 --> 01:11:56,840
By imagining the world, the world becomes alive.
通过想象世界，世界就变得有生气。

1256
01:11:57,180 --> 01:11:58,560
So, the greater our imagination,
于是，想象越大，想象就越有生气。

1257
01:11:58,960 --> 01:12:01,480
the more alive our imagination becomes.
而这点在画中最直观地表现出来。

1258
01:12:01,880 --> 01:12:06,640
And this idea is most visually expressed in the painting,
And this idea is most visually expressed in the painting,

1259
01:12:06,760 --> 01:12:10,620
The Creation of Adam, by Michelangelo, okay?
《创世亚当》由米开朗创作，好吗？

1260
01:12:11,120 --> 01:12:12,460
This is Michelangelo.
这就是米开朗。

1261
01:12:13,140 --> 01:12:14,440
The Creation of Adam.
《创世亚当》。

1262
01:12:14,820 --> 01:12:18,620
And so, this goes back to the story of how God created Adam.
于是，这回到上帝创造亚当的故事。

1263
01:12:19,460 --> 01:12:21,920
God created Adam out of dust, and
上帝用尘土造亚当，且……

1264
01:12:21,920 --> 01:12:25,620
he breathed the essence of life into Adam, okay?
并把生命的精气吹入亚当。

1265
01:12:26,120 --> 01:12:30,460
Now, there are two ways of looking at this painting, okay?
现在，有两种方式来看这幅画，好吗？

1266
01:12:30,660 --> 01:12:32,920
There are two ways of understanding the title, The Creation of Adam.
有两种方式来理解标题《创世亚当》。”

1267
01:12:33,180 --> 01:12:36,380
You can first understand it in the typical way, which
你可以先按典型方式理解，……

1268
01:12:36,380 --> 01:12:40,080
is that God created Adam, and that they are equals, okay?
是的，神造了亚当，且他们是平等的，行吗？

1269
01:12:40,180 --> 01:12:44,040
You can see that these two worlds, the creation of Adam, and God, they're almost equal.
你可以看到这两个世界，亚当的创造和神，几乎是平等的。

1270
01:12:44,200 --> 01:12:47,460
We are equal to God. But then you can change perspective,
我们与神平等。但随后你可以换个视角。

1271
01:12:47,620 --> 01:12:49,800
and you can say, the creation of Adam really means
并且你可以说，亚当的创造真正意味着

1272
01:12:50,480 --> 01:12:52,340
God is Adam's creation.
神是亚当的创造物。

1273
01:12:53,660 --> 01:12:56,240
God is what we created from our imagination,
神是我们从想象中创造的。

1274
01:12:56,620 --> 01:13:02,580
all right? Now, you can see God is surrounded by his angels,
一切都对吗？现在，你可以看到神被他的天使包围着，

1275
01:13:02,840 --> 01:13:06,420
okay? But you take them away, and what do you have behind them?
好了？但你把它们拿走，背后你得到什么？

1276
01:13:07,280 --> 01:13:11,460
Guys, this is a picture of the human brain, right?
伙计们，这是一幅人脑的图，没错吧？

1277
01:13:11,460 --> 01:13:14,880
Do you see this? Okay, this is a stem, okay?
你看见这个了吗？好了，这是一根干，好的？

1278
01:13:14,980 --> 01:13:17,400
And this is the human brain, okay?
而这就是人脑，好的？

1279
01:13:17,480 --> 01:13:21,380
You take them away, and hidden behind is the human brain, right?
你把它们拿走，隐藏在后面的是人脑，对吗？

1280
01:13:21,680 --> 01:13:23,340
Which means what? Which means that
哪意味着什么？哪意味着……

1281
01:13:23,340 --> 01:13:26,520
God is an emanation from our imagination,
上帝是我们想象的衍生物，

1282
01:13:26,960 --> 01:13:28,360
okay?
好了？

1283
01:13:29,160 --> 01:13:33,680
Not the true God. The true God is like light itself,
不是那真神。真神就像光本身，吧？

1284
01:13:33,880 --> 01:13:38,000
right? Love itself, okay? But this God has given us a capacity to imagine,
爱本身，好的？但这神赐给我们想象的能力，

1285
01:13:38,140 --> 01:13:41,040
so we've imagined another God to be,
于是我们想象了另一位神

1286
01:13:41,040 --> 01:13:45,280
to take place of the real God, okay?
取代真正的神，好的？

1287
01:13:45,340 --> 01:13:48,400
Do you understand? So the real God is the human imagination,
你明白了吗？于是真正的神就是人类的想象，

1288
01:13:49,220 --> 01:13:50,780
the human brain, the human mind.
人类的大脑，人类的心智。

1289
01:13:51,580 --> 01:13:53,420
That's what gives life to the universe, okay?
这就是赋予宇宙生命的原因，吧？

1290
01:13:53,760 --> 01:13:55,100
So this, if you think about it,
所以这件事，如果你思考一下，

1291
01:13:55,180 --> 01:14:00,160
it is a radical revolution in human intellectual history.
它是人类知识史上的一次根本革命。

1292
01:14:00,900 --> 01:14:02,480
You guys, do you know where this painting is?
你们知道这幅画在哪里吗？

1293
01:14:03,240 --> 01:14:08,620
This painting is on the top of something called the Sistine Chapel in the Vatican.
这幅画在梵蒂冈的西斯廷教堂顶部。

1294
01:14:10,380 --> 01:14:12,880
It's at the Vatican. It's at the very heart of the Catholic Church.
它在梵蒂冈，正是天主教会的心脏。

1295
01:14:13,600 --> 01:14:16,140
So what Darnay has been able to do
于是达纳伊所能做到的事

1296
01:14:16,140 --> 01:14:21,520
is destroy an empire peacefully for the power of poetry,
是用诗歌的力量，平静地摧毁一个帝国，

1297
01:14:22,220 --> 01:14:25,060
for subtlety, for the power of love.
用细腻与爱的力量

1298
01:14:25,580 --> 01:14:28,940
Darnay was able to influence Michelangelo, who was able to take his ideas
达纳伊能够影响米开朗，米开朗又把他的想法植入天主教会的心脏，

1299
01:14:28,940 --> 01:14:34,000
and then plant his ideas within the very heart of the Catholic Church,
随后把这些想法植入天主教会的心脏，

1300
01:14:34,180 --> 01:14:36,140
and thus reinvent the Catholic Church.
从而重新塑造了天主教会。

1301
01:14:36,360 --> 01:14:37,800
That is the power of love.
那就是爱的力量。

1302
01:14:37,920 --> 01:14:40,040
That is the power of imagination, right?
那就是想象的力量，对吧？

1303
01:14:41,700 --> 01:14:44,780
Great. Okay, any questions?
好的，任何问题吗？

1304
01:14:53,480 --> 01:14:55,140
Okay, so think of some questions.
好的，先想想几个问题。

1305
01:14:55,600 --> 01:15:00,400
Next class, we will do the Protestant Reformation, okay?
下节课我们来讲新教改革，好吗？
